claim.claim-text:
20. A printed sheet product comprising:
a planar and generally rectangular body having two opposing major sides defining an outer perimeter of the body, the major sides having length of about three and three-eighths inches and a width of about two and one-eighth inch perpendicular the length, the body including printing visible on at least one of the two major sides and the body further including an opening extending through the body and the two major planar sides so as to permit attachment of the body to a key holding member;
at least one unique code on at least a first of the two major sides of the body, the code uniquely identifying the element from other elements having at least some of the same printing and other different codes, the code being located on the first major side proximal a first outer perimeter edge of the body between the opening and the first outer perimeter edge, the code being readable by swiping the code and first outer perimeter edge of the body through a swipe reader machine capable of reading the unique code; and
scoring through the generally rectangular body defining a first planar identification element removable from a remainder of the generally rectangular body, the first removable element including at least the opening and the unique code;
wherein the scoring further defines a second planar identification element in the printed sheet product, the second identification element also including the at least one unique code, the printed sheet product including a flexible sheet material core and a first flexible material sheet covering permanently applied to a first major side of the sheet material core, each of the first identification element and the releasably joined second identification element including separate portions of a single piece of the sheet material core.

